snippet.textDisplay:
The only thought on my Sufi mind:
Let my Medina be here and now,
wherever You will me to flutter.

This Sufi shall not stray,
rooted in the wish to be here, now—
free of the mind,
a simple prayer to be the wind I am.

Osho whispers: “Life exists only in this moment.
Drop the mind’s chase for past and future;
become a flute for existence to play its song.”

Buddha smiles: “The secret of awakening lies in presence.
What is past is gone,
what is future is unseen—
only now blooms the lotus of life.”

Guru Nanak sings: “Why wander in search of Him afar?
He is here, within,
if you rest in the stillness of this breath.”

In this sacred now,
where words emerge and dissolve,
may I dissolve too—
into the silence of being.

One of my favorites.
